@page "/about-course"
@layout EmptyLayout

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>About Course</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/bootstrap/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            background: #f5f5f5;
            font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        .container {
            background: #fff;
            margin-top: 50px;
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 25px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h2 {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            color: #337ab7;
        }

        .icon {
            font-size: 40px;
            color: #5bc0de;
            margin-right: 20px;
        }

        .section {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 22px;
            color: #333;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .section p {
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .back-btn {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="text-right back-btn">
            <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="history.back();">
                <i class="fa fa-arrow-left"></i> Back
            </button>
        </div>

        <h2><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> About the Course</h2>

        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title"><i class="fa fa-graduation-cap icon"></i> Course Overview</div>
            <p>This course is designed to equip students and officers with a deep understanding of contemporary military strategy, leadership principles, and operational tactics. Participants will engage in both theoretical and practical modules that foster analytical thinking and command capabilities.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title"><i class="fa fa-calendar icon"></i> Duration & Structure</div>
            <p>The course spans a period of 6 to 12 months, depending on the track selected. Each term includes lectures, workshops, field exercises, and evaluations. Weekly assessments and simulations help ensure knowledge retention and readiness for real-world scenarios.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <div class="section-title"><i class="fa fa-certificate icon"></i> Certification</div>
            <p>Upon successful completion, participants will receive an accredited certificate recognized by national defense institutions. High-performing candidates may also receive commendation letters from senior faculty members.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

